&lt;div class=&quot;markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Marketing is a strategic leader responsible for developing, implementing, and executing comprehensive marketing strategies to drive revenue, increase brand awareness, and enhance the overall guest experience. This role requires a creative and analytical individual with a deep understanding of the hospitality industry and a proven track record of successful marketing campaigns. The Director of Marketing is responsible for all marketing channels, including digital, traditional, public relations, and social media, to position the hotel as a premier destination. The ideal candidate will be a strategic thinker and a hands-on doer, capable of managing multiple projects and collaborating effectively with various departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Marketing &amp;amp; Planning:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a robust annual marketing plan aligned with the hotel and restaurant&#39;s business goals and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify new opportunities and stay ahead of industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define target audiences and develop tailored marketing strategies to reach them effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the revenue management and sales teams to create integrated strategies for increasing bookings, group sales, and F&amp;amp;B revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Management &amp;amp; Public Relations:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and elevate the hotel and restaurant brand identity across all channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage the brand&#39;s voice, messaging, and visual standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all public relations activities, including press releases, media relations, and crisis communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate relationships with key media outlets, influencers, and industry partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Marketing &amp;amp; E-commerce:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and optimize all digital marketing channels, including the hotel and restaurant websites, social media platforms (e.g., Instagram, LinkedIn), and email marketing campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute paid advertising campaigns (e.g., PPC, display ads, social media ads) to drive direct bookings and restaurant reservations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze website traffic, campaign performance, and other digital metrics using tools like Google Analytics to measure ROI and inform future strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage online reputation and guest reviews on platforms like TripAdvisor, Google, and Yelp.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Creation &amp;amp; Management:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality, engaging content, including photography, video, blog posts, and marketing collateral.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a content calendar and ensure consistent and timely content delivery across all platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the management of marketing assets and brand-approved materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promotions &amp;amp; Partnerships:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute promotions, packages, and special events to drive business during off-peak seasons and holidays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and negotiate co-marketing and partnership opportunities with local businesses, tourism boards, and event organizers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budgeting &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the annual marketing budget, ensuring all spending is tracked, allocated efficiently, and provides a strong return on investment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present regular performance reports to the executive team, highlighting key metrics, successes, and areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with the General Manager, F&amp;amp;B Director, Sales Director, and other department heads to ensure marketing efforts are integrated and effective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Marketing, Communications, Hospitality Management, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5-7 years of experience in a marketing role, with at least 2-3 years in a leadership position within the hospitality industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in digital marketing, social media management, and public relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret data and make data-driven decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A creative and innovative mindset with a passion for storytelling and brand building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with marketing software, analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics), and social media management platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously in an agile environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to be part of a luxury hotel experience that exemplifies excellence in service and hospitality.&lt;/p&gt;
